  p.lead.question Why is there a charge for travel on my invoice?
  p
    |
      Most companies that provide on the road services do charge separately for
      travel. Those that don’t charge for travel separately are making it up
      somewhere else in their pricing structure, usually with an inflated
      service charge or hourly rate. Our clients tend to side with us,
      preferring transparency in our billing. Plus, if your neighbor becomes a
      client on your route, we adjust your travel charge down in kind, resulting
      in a visible discount on every bill.

